{"word":"συνελίσσω","slug":"συνελίσσω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>συνελίσσω</b></el> <el>(ionic <el>συν-ειλ</el>) (attic <el>-ττω</el>) (<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>ξω</el>) </el><p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to roll together</i>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to involve oneself in</i> a thing, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:intransitive'>intr.</a> <i>to coil itself up</i>, of a serpent, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}